column2: Repo / Reverse Repo Auctions under the Liquidity Adjustment Facility (LAF)

#       :  Outstanding amount is shown along with fortnight Repo and 28-day Repo. 
**      :   Fixed rate LAF Repo. 
+       :  Special fixed rate term repo. 
##     :  Under forex swap facility. 
@     :   Net of Repo. 
$        :  Second LAF auction introduced with effect from November 28, 2005 and discontinued with effect from August 2007. It was reintroduced on Reporting Fridays with effect from August 1, 2008, and from September 17, 2008 on a daily basis. Since May 6, 2009 it is being conducted only on Reporting Fridays.
$$      :  Additional LAF auction on March 31, 2006, March 14, 2008, March 17, 2008 and March 31, 2008. 
$$$    :  Special LAF conducted on 18.01.2008. 

Note : With effect from October 29, 2004, nomenclature of Repo and Reverse Repo has been interchanged as per international usages. Till October 28, 2004, Repo indicated absorption of liquidity where Reverse Repo meant injection of liquidity by the Reserve Bank.
